text: Patriarch Athanasius II may refer to: * Athanasius II of Alexandria, Patriarch of Alexandria in 490–496 * Athanasius II, Patriarch of Antioch (ruled in 683–686) * Athanasius II of Constantinople, Ecumenical Patriarch in 1450–1453 * Athanasius II Dabbas, Melkite Greek Patriarch of Antioch in 1611–1619
title: Patriarch Athanasius II
